<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>4<percent/> of 1516</li> 
<li>27<percent/> of 249</li> 
<li>85<percent/> of 10</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>B: 27<percent/> of 249</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{85}\%\cdot{10}={8.5}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{27}\%\cdot{249}={67.23}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4}\%\cdot{1516}={60.64}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 27<percent/> of 249 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>